death of the old gods 
- 
- 
-

the air they breathed must have been the most fresh, the colors they saw must have been the most vibrant, 
the world they knew and lived in had everything any could want, ask, desire, envy. What wonder must have 
been in their eyes, hidden, tucked away for only the privilege few, those who would pay with all they had, 
to possess. 
 Perhpas it was just not for me to know, to know what they knew, to even know them. This world around me, 
 is what I knew, whether it knew me or not, only sometimes I could say. 
 
 their thoughts their feelings their hopes and all of thier dreams, so held deep within me, fast was its grip. 
 I could not break away, it filled every pore, every vesicle of my lungs.

General talking in the war room:
 They are emboldended by the riot 
 the rebellion only grows their plight. It must be snuffed out now, if we ever hope to take the western corridor

"A new world". That's what I was told, that is what we were promised. So why is that as she sits here, 
dust smeared, heart broken, destitute, I find my self in such a state of confusion (sarcastic tone) ? 
I'll tell you why, with half grin, chuckle, rhtorical remarks, "it's because ... " 

I tried to protect everyone, but in the end, I could protect no one, not even myself.
